udy, also contains a variety of significant Middle English texts. They range from the religious and devotional: a Wycliffite New Testament, Love's Mirror, and Heinrich Suso's treatise The Seven Points of True Love and Everlasting Wisdom); to the scientific and medicinal: Chaucer's Astrolabe, Henry Daniel's Liber Uricrisiarum; and to the historical, notably the Brut and Mandeville's Travels. Patrick J. Horner, FSC (a De LaSalle Christian Brother) is Professor of English at Manhattan College.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish prose literatureyMiddle English, 1100-1500xManuscriptsvCatalogs. 0aManuscripts, English (Middle)zEnglandzOxfordvCatalogs. 4aBibliography & Manuscripts. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aREFERENCE / Bibliographies & Indexes.2bisacsh  aBodleian Library.  aHistorical Documents.  aLincoln Cathedral.  aManuscripts.  aMedieval Literature.  aMedieval Manuscripts.  aMiddle English Prose.  aRichard Britnell.1 aHorner, Patrick J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311143136940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204265540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782042655423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782042655/original  a978-3-11-143136-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles